HEADWORD: Pelorus
<hw>Pe*lo"rus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[After
<ets>Pelorus</ets>, said to have been Hannibal's pilot when he left
Italy.]</ety> <fld>(Navig.)</fld> <def>An instrument similar to a
mariner's compass, but without magnetic needles, and having two sight
vanes by which bearings are taken, esp. such as cannot be taken by the
compass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pelota</ent>⟦br⟧
